## 🤔 What is this?
Just some agent skills I hacked together to run [MLE-bench](https://github.com/openai/mle-bench). 
Mostly a record of my dark history wrestling with AI agents. There's a lot of duct-taped code here just to meet deadlines. It probably won't run, or if it does, the performance is absolute trash.

## 📂 What's inside?
- A bunch of scripts with probably hidden bugs.
- Test docs (some might still contain my 3 AM mental breakdown comments).
- `mission_skills/`: The main code lives here, but I haven't figured out how to refactor it elegantly yet. The current architecture is basically spaghetti 🍝.

## 🚀 How to run? (Mostly writing this so I don't forget)
1. Clone this mess:
   ```bash
   git clone git@github.com:Celsia-Typo/mle-skill.git

```

2. Install dependencies (honestly I forgot exactly what's required, just `pip install` whatever it complains about...)
3. Close your eyes, put your hands together, run the tests, and pray you don't get another `IndexError` or `KeyError`.

